  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (ML surrogate)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for an ML-augmented CFD hemolysis prediction pipeline for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether a neural-network surrogate model trained on high-fidelity CFD data can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. A feedforward neural network (three hidden layers, ReLU activations) was trained to map pump geometry and operating-point parameters to relative hemolysis index (RHI). Two training runs with different random seeds were executed and reported to show reproducibility; both runs achieved RHI prediction error below 3% on the held-out test set, and agreement between the two runs was characterised as 'excellent' by the assessment team. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2).",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/cpb-hemolysis-rhl-criterion",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cpb-ml-surrogate-worst-case-hemolysis",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/ffnn-rhi-surrogate-v2",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-cbp-cfd-training-set-v1",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-cbp-cfd-holdout-set-v1"
  ],
  "hasContextOfUse": {
    "decisionConsequence": "High",
    "description": "A CFD model is used to evaluate the sensitivity of pump-induced hemolysis to variations in component dimensions for a centrifugal blood pump used during cardiopulmonary bypass surgery. Model influence is MEDIUM (testing confirms results); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect tolerance decision could impact clinical hemolysis levels). Model Risk Level 2.",
    "deviceClass": "Class II",
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou1-cpb",
    "intendedUse": "Use CFD to identify worst-case operating conditions for hemolysis across 5 flow-speed combinations for a Class II CPB device. Results compared against predicate device hemolysis using relative hemolysis index (RH < 1 acceptance criterion).",
    "modelInfluence": "Medium",
    "name": "COU1: Cardiopulmonary bypass use (Class II)",
    "type": "ContextOfUse"
  },
  "hasValidationResult": [
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/ffnn-rhi-seed42-test-performance",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "FFNN RHI surrogate — seed 42 test-set performance",
      "description": "The neural-network surrogate was trained with random seed 42 on 4,800 CFD-derived operating-point samples. On the 600-sample held-out test set the model achieved mean absolute error (MAE) = 0.0021 RHI units, RMSE = 0.0034 RHI units, and R² = 0.9971. Maximum point-wise error across all five target flow-speed combinations was 2.8%, below the 3% acceptance threshold. The model correctly ranked worst-case operating conditions in 100% of evaluated geometry variants."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/ffnn-rhi-seed137-test-performance",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "FFNN RHI surrogate — seed 137 test-set performance",
      "description": "A second training run using random seed 137 was conducted to demonstrate reproducibility. This run achieved MAE = 0.0023 RHI units, RMSE = 0.0036 RHI units, and R² = 0.9968 on the same held-out test set. The assessment team noted that both runs produced 'excellent agreement' and that worst-case operating-condition rankings were identical between the two seeds. On this basis the surrogate was deemed sufficiently stable for regulatory submission. No statistical characterisation of seed-to-seed prediction variance (e.g., confidence intervals, standard deviation across seeds, or ensemble spread) was performed or reported."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/ffnn-rhi-physical-plausibility",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Physical plausibility check — RHI vs. shear-stress correlation",
      "description": "Surrogate RHI predictions were compared against volume-averaged shear-stress fields from independent CFD runs at three operating points not included in training. The correlation coefficient between surrogate-predicted RHI and CFD-derived power-law hemolysis index was 0.994, confirming that the model captures the dominant physical mechanism. No seed-variance envelope was propagated through this plausibility check."
    }
  ],
