      "acceptanceCriteria": "In-vitro hemolysis experiments conducted at the five target flow-speed combinations under ISO 10993-4 conditions; blood analogue fluid properties match CFD boundary conditions within 5%.",
      "rationale": "Bench-top hemolysis experiments were performed at all five COU flow-speed combinations using a bovine-blood analogue (glycerol-water, viscosity 3.5 mPa·s at 37°C). Fluid properties agreed with CFD inputs to within 2.3%. Experimental RHI values were used as the primary validation reference for the surrogate output layer."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Surrogate-predicted RHI agrees with experimental RHI within ±10% at all five operating points; worst-case operating condition correctly identified.",
      "rationale": "Surrogate predictions (seed 42 model) were compared against experimental RHI at all five operating points. Agreement ranged from 1.2% to 7.8%, within the ±10% acceptance band. The worst-case operating condition (3.5 L/min, 3200 RPM) was correctly identified by the surrogate. The seed 137 model produced identical worst-case identification. Point-estimate metrics from both seeds were reported as evidence of reproducibility; no distributional characterisation of inter-seed variance was included."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
