      "acceptanceCriteria": "Surrogate output (RHI) is the regulatory quantity of interest; surrogate input features are the same geometric and operating-point parameters used in the COU decision.",
      "rationale": "The surrogate directly predicts the relative hemolysis index (RHI) used in the RH < 1 acceptance criterion. Input features — impeller tip clearance, volute width, flow rate, and rotational speed — are the exact parameters varied in the tolerance sensitivity study. The QoI mapping is therefore fully aligned with the COU decision."
    },
    {
